Risk 1: weak authentication this allows hackers of any sort get into peoples data with no problems and it can put people in danger 
risk 2: Malware-infected devices a VPN will be able to be hacked if you have malware that was already on your device and a lot of malware is able to remain under the radar without you knowing for weeks months or even years
risk 3: Over-permissive access this can lead to the hacker not just getting into your device/devices they most likely have a masterkey and anything they need to ruin your life
and steal your money and private info and data
